sql:
SELECT title
FROM movies
ORDER BY title;

SELECT title
FROM movies
ORDER BY release_year, title;

external_knowledge:
- The term "difference in ratings" refers to the difference between IMDB and Rotten Tomatoes ratings; 
- The phrase "top movies" refers to the top 5 movies with the highest average difference in ratings; 
- "Cumulative difference in ratings" refers to the total difference in ratings for each genre, calculated by summing the average difference in ratings for each movie within the genre.
